<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="565" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,402,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,690,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length forewing 21.5–25.8 mm in male (25.6 mm in 
<typeStatus box="[927,1027,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">holotype</typeStatus>
) and 25–28.7 mm in female. In general 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[200,313,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[200,313,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[320,383,727,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[320,383,727,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1923" box="[582,693,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurelia">
<emphasis box="[582,693,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. aurelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[708,837,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–20" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1817,1841]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,181,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[246,1342,181,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–20. Adults of Agalope spp. 11, Agalope owadai sp. n., male, HT, Bomi, Xizang, ZSY222 (CHSY); 12, ditto, male, PT, Bomi, Xizang, BMAG1 (CHSY); 13, ditto, male, PT, Tongmai, Xizang, TMAG1 (CHSY); 14, ditto, male, PT, Jiali, Xizang, JLAG1 (CHSY); 15, ditto, female, PT, Tongmai, Xizang, TMAG2 (CHSY); 16, A. aurelia, male, Gongshan, Yunnan, (CHSY); 17, ditto, GSAG1 (CHSY); 18, ditto, female, Dulongjiang, Yunnan, DLJAG1 (CHSY); 19, ditto, male, syntype, Bahand, Yunnan (NHMUK), by courtesy of Dr. Mamoru Owada; 20, ditto, female, syntype, Bahand, Yunnan (NHMUK), by courtesy of Dr. Mamoru Owada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854082/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Figs 16–20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[848,921,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[206,1375,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[198,1389,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Male genitalia of Agalope spp. 39, Agalope owadai sp. n., HT, slide ZSY222; 40, ditto, PT, slide TMAG1; 41, ditto, PT, slide BMAG1; 42, ditto, PT, slide JLAG1; 43, A. aurelia, slide GSAG1; 44, ditto, slide GSAG2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854094/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">43, 44</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[932,1003,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–50" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[182,1409,194,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[166,1422,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 45–50. Magnified images of juxta of Agalope spp. 45, Agalope owadai sp. n., HT, slide ZSY222; 46, ditto, PT, slide TMAG1; 47, ditto, PT, slide BMAG1; 48, ditto, PT, slide JLAG1; 49, A. aurelia, slide GSAG1; 50, ditto, slide GSAG2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854100/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">49, 50</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1015,1044,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–61" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1345,181,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[220,1367,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 57–61. Female genitalia of Agalope spp. 57, Agalope haoi sp. n., PT, slide ZSY221; 58, A. wangi, PT, slide NS- MT2167f, after Owada (1992) with corpus bursae outlined by black; 59, A. owadai sp. n., PT, slide TMAG2; 60, A. aurelia, slide DLJAG1; 61, A. lucia, slide GSAG3. Arrows in figs 57 and 58 indicating the 8th tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854106/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">60</figureCitation>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[1119,1208,727,753]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1289,727,753]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">China</collectingCountry>
, but it can be easily distinguished from the latter by the combination of the following characters: 1) darkish pattern of forewing from the postmedial to marginal section of the wing is paler and less contrasting with the ground color; 2) lobes of the bifurcate juxta are covered by larger spinules laterally and dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1143,834,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–50" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[182,1409,194,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[166,1422,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 45–50. Magnified images of juxta of Agalope spp. 45, Agalope owadai sp. n., HT, slide ZSY222; 46, ditto, PT, slide TMAG1; 47, ditto, PT, slide BMAG1; 48, ditto, PT, slide JLAG1; 49, A. aurelia, slide GSAG1; 50, ditto, slide GSAG2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854100/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Figs 45–48</figureCitation>
); while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1923" box="[1266,1379,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurelia">
<emphasis box="[1266,1379,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. aurelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are covered by smaller spinules laterally and much lesser and smaller ones dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1253,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–50" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[182,1409,194,1451]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[166,1422,181,1468]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 45–50. Magnified images of juxta of Agalope spp. 45, Agalope owadai sp. n., HT, slide ZSY222; 46, ditto, PT, slide TMAG1; 47, ditto, PT, slide BMAG1; 48, ditto, PT, slide JLAG1; 49, A. aurelia, slide GSAG1; 50, ditto, slide GSAG2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854100/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Figs 49, 50</figureCitation>
); 3) aedeagus is significantly more slender medially and distally; 4) corpus bursae is much smaller with signa weakly sclerotized, smaller and obsolete, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1923" box="[496,608,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurelia">
<emphasis box="[496,608,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. aurelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the corpus bursae is much larger with signum strongly sclerotized, larger and prominent. 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,512,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[329,512,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Agalope owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[520,584,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[520,584,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is also superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[931,1086,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chayuensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[931,1086,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. chayuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1094,1158,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1094,1158,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
described above and the comparison has been made in the diagnosis of the former species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="565" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,402,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1050,1076]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from Bomi (
<figureCitation box="[593,676,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[151,1435,181,1851]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Habitats and living adult of Agalope spp. in P.R. China. 62, Pianma, Lushui, Western Yunnan; 63, Samage, Weixi, Northwestern Yunnan; 64, Gongshan, Nujiang Lisu Autonomous Prefecture, Western Yunnan; 65, living adult of A. aurelia, resting on leaves, Gongshan; 66, Longgu Village, Chayu, Southeastern Xizang; 67, Taohuagou, Bomi, Southeastern Xizang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854108/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) and Jiali Counties in Southeastern and Eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[1228,1312,1051,1077]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, P. R. 
<collectingCountry name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="565" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,402,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1123,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[579,661,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai">
<emphasis box="[579,661,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dedicated to the Japanese lepidopterologist Dr. Mamoru Owada, who is also an expert in the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[614,759,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chalcosiinae">Chalcosiinae</taxonomicName>
and encouraged the first author to continue his study on this intriguing subfamily.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="565" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,402,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">Remarks.</emphasis>
Individual variation in the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[822,935,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[822,935,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">A. owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[944,1008,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[944,1008,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="565" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has been observed in the depth of the notch at the distal end of uncus and juxta, length of the juxta and the distal saccular process as well as the size and shape of posterior tegumenal projection. However, externally these individuals are uniform in wing pattern, and the aedeagi are also rather constant, which lead us to consider all of them conspecific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
